<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 84 Charing Cross Road (Disney Sunday at 11 p.m.), a 1987 celebration of the 
life of the imagination, stars Anne Bancroft as Manhattan writer Helene 
Hanff.Bancroft's Helene becomes caught up in an extraordinary epistolary 
relationship with a London book dealer (Anthony Hopkins). 
</P>
<P>
 Mike's Murder (KCOP Saturday at 2:30 a.m.), James Bridges' overlooked, 
disquieting 1984 thriller, tours the highs and lows of the cocaine trade. With 
Debra Winger, Mark Keyloun and, unforgettably, Darrell Larson. 
</P>
