</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re the finale of "Star Trek: The Next Generation": What a disappointment the 
final episode was. The plot was inconsistent with the characters' development 
of the last seven years. Although it is likely that Picard and Crusher marry, 
it is unlikely a man who is an expert in diplomacy would fail at his own 
marriage. 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Lane, Rowland Heights 
