<HEADLINE>
<P>
'SEINFELD': THE REALITY SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I disagree completely with Matthew Okada who asked, "What's so great about 
'Seinfeld'?" (TV Times, May 22). I'll tell you what's so great about 
"Seinfeld": It's the best-written, most sophisticated and funniest show on TV, 
and in its random disjointedness it is the sitcom that is closest to real life. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Showstack, Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061294-0032 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 050523 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
June 12, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
