<TEXT>
<P>
 WILDERNESS ABOVE THE SOUND: The Story of Mount Ranier National Park by Arthur 
D. Martinson (Roberts Rinehart: $11.95; 76 pp.) . Martinson traces the history 
of one of America's first National Parks in this slim volume. The spectacular 
beauty of the volcanic cone and surrounding forests inspired a preservation 
campaign that lead to its protection from development in 1893. Martinson 
supplements his narration of the struggle to maintain the park in its natural 
state while admitting increasing numbers of visitors with a wonderful array of 
turn-of-the-century photographs. 
</P>
