</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE MEN IN MY LIFE AND OTHER MORE OR LESS TRUE RECOLLECTIONS OF KINSHIP by 
James D. Houston (Greywolf Press: $12; 160 pp., paperback original). Houston 
tackles what are currently referred to as "guy things" in these introspective 
essays. His reflections on gaining respect from his college football team 
mates, rejecting the sham friendship produced by fraternity hazing and finding 
common ground with his father through music have more relevance to the lives of 
a healthy male in contemporary society than the drum-banging, role-playing 
games of the so-called men's movement. 
