</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE GENIUS OF DESIRE by Brian Bouldrey (Ballantine: $10; 274 pp.) . Bouldrey's 
first novel depicts a young man's coming of age in a weird Southern family 
dominated by a cadre of strong-willed females who style themselves "the Kaiser 
Broads." Bouldrey skillfully captures the claustrophobic discomfort of a small 
town during a humid summer, when the residents long for fresh air -- literally 
and metaphorically. Against this confining background, the narrator experiences 
his first tentative encounters with death and desire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
