</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LAKE COUNTRY: A Series of Journeys by Kathleen Stocking (University of 
Michigan Press: 229 pp., paperback original). Stocking explores Michigan's 
Upper Peninsula in these intimate accounts of wandering the shores of the Great 
Lakes, listening to debates over development and following roads no longer 
traveled. After leaving a lonely island in Lake Huron, she realizes, "The 
thought of being home, feeding the animals, calling my neighbors, getting Gaia 
ready for school in the morning, seems comforting, like a lamp in a window on a 
dark night." Her agreeable prose falters when she stumbles into PC postures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
