<P>
 *** Madder Rose, "Panic On," Atlantic/Seed. On the New York quartet's second 
album, torrents of spiraling guitar distortion slip under Mary Lorson's 
harmonious and nonchalant vocals.The band borrows cool moods from the Velvet 
Underground but drops in its own smeared pop appeal. The vocals are not wafting 
and sweet but bruised and streetwise, and the music, though laden with 
beautiful guitar work, is too savvy to be sappy. 
