<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERMANENT WAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thirty years ago my husband and I saw "Endless Summer" at the drive-in 
theater. We were not surfers, nor were we kids at the time, but we absolutely 
loved that movie ("If Everybody Had an Ocean . . . ," by Kalle Matso and Scott 
White, May 29). 
</P>
<P>
 I'm now a grandmother, still don't surf, but can't wait to see "Endless Summer 
II." It is the energy, power and possible danger of the waves, the glorious 
scenery and summer days and the dreams, perseverance and athleticism of the 
surfers that make these movies not just attractive to those who surf. 
</P>
<P>
 Yes, there is a non-surfer following for "Endless Summer II," just as there 
was for "Endless Summer," and I as one non-surfer will eagerly await seeing 
"Endless Summer III." 
</P>
<P>
 RUTH JOHNSTON 
</P>
<P>
 Panorama City 
</P>
