<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Put shut-off valves on all your hoses to conserve water. 
</P>
<P>
 * Feed houseplants on a monthly basis. It's their biggest growing season 
thanks to brighter light and more warmth. 
</P>
<P>
 * Set your mower blades higher. Use 2-to-2 1/2 inches for bluegrass lawns, 2 
1/2 to 3 inches for tall fescue, and 1 inch for warm season lawns such as 
bermuda and Zoysia. 
</P>
<P>
 * Prepare for the first day of summer by planting hot weather annuals. 
</P>
