<P>
UCLA'S ROTC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Many of life's choices and avenues foster uniqueness and individuality. The 
military and ROTC do not.Cohesiveness and cooperation demand conformity and 
uniformity -- hence, the precision drills, marching in lines, the haircuts and 
uniforms. This environment is not the place for heterosexuals or homosexuals, 
to demand their freedom to "let me be me." 
</P>
<P>
 The military Establishment justly and fairly discriminates against anyone who 
"stands out" from the troops. No sign reads "Gays need not apply." ROTC has one 
consistent high standard: "Sore thumbs" of any kind not welcome here. 
</P>
<P>
