<P>
FAIRCHILD PAYS U.S. IN CLAIMS INVOLVING UNTESTED FASTENERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Defense contractor Fairchild Industries Inc. has paid the government $330,000 
to settle claims that it sold untested or improperly tested aerospace fasteners 
-- such as nuts and bolts -- to the military, the Justice Department said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Federal prosecutors accused the Chantilly, Va.-based company of failing to 
