<HEADLINE>
<P>
RABBI SCHNEERSON, LUBAVITCHER LEADER, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rabbi Menachem Schneerson, who transformed the ultra-Orthodox Lubavitcher 
movement into a major force in Judaism, died today at age 92. 
</P>
<P>
 Schneerson, the grand rabbi of the Lubavitchers since 1950, died at 1:50 a.m. 
EDT in Beth Israel Medical Center, shortly after the Jewish Sabbath ended, said 
Rabbi Yehuda Krinksy, spokesman for the sect. 
</P>
<P>
 Schneerson had suffered a stroke in March, 1992, and another one March 10. 
</P>
<P>
 A more detailed obituary on Rabbi Menachem Schneerson will appear in Monday's 
editions of The Times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
