<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA PALMA HOSPITAL TO OFFER CPR TRAINING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Palma Intercommunity Hospital will conduct training for older adults in 
cardiopulmonary resuscitation on June 24 from 8 a.m. to noon in the main 
classroom at the hospital, 7901 Walker St. 
</P>
<P>
 The training is open to anyone 55 or older. The four-hour instruction course 
is being co-sponsored by the American Heart Assn. Participants will receive 
training using specially equipped manikins, and certificates will be awarded to 
those completing the training. 
</P>
<P>
 The $10 fee for the course includes materials. Registration and prepayment 
must be made by Friday. To register, call the hospital's community education 
reservation line at (714) 670-6066 or (310) 921-4120, Ext. 6066. 
</P>
