<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF CLUB PROJECT MAY ENCOURAGE GROWTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Assemblyman Richard Katz, D-Panorama City, opposes a 355-acre Cosmo World 
Inc. project with an international golf club in Big Tununga Wash (Valley 
Commentary, May 29). 
</P>
<P>
 I disagree with Mr. Katz.Being a 30-year native of the Sunland/Hansen Dam 
area, I have witnessed the plight of the dam and the wash. The Hansen Dam area 
was once nice for a Sunday outing, with family picnics, water skiing, swimming 
and fishing. It has since been reduced to a mudhole with the annoying roar and 
dust of the constant excavation. 
</P>
<P>
 Assemblyman Katz refers to developers who care little about natural beauty. To 
him, natural beauty must mean weeds, broken fences, abandoned cars and 
appliances, along with the use of the roadside as a public dump. 
</P>
<P>
 With a project of this magnitude, I see nothing but growth and prosperity for 
the Sunland area, growth that complements and enhances its equestrian 
lifestyle. 
</P>
<P>
 ALBERT OBREGON 
</P>
<P>
 Sunland 
</P>
