<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOBY-TRAPPED ONION PATCH KILLS OWNER, SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man and his son were electrocuted by a booby trap they had set up to protect 
their onion patch against thieves, a Bucharest newspaper said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Florian Iorga, 42, and his 16-year-old son, Aurel, were found dead Friday in 
their pajamas among the onions behind their Bucharest house, the daily 
Evenimentul Zilei said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two were searching the garden after hearing noises in the night and 
evidently stepped on the wires. Iorga set the trap after thieves had stolen 
onions and threatened him with violence when he reported them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
