<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAIN DECAPITATES BOY ON TRESTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 11-year-old boy who was fishing with companions off a railroad bridge in 
Pico Rivera was decapitated by a passing freight train Saturday as he tried to 
race to safety. 
</P>
<P>
 The 3,600-foot-long freight had come out of a sharp curve near Whittier 
Boulevard about 1:40 p.m. and was about to cross the bridge over the San 
Gabriel River when the engineer spotted the six youngsters on the trestle. 
</P>
<P>
 The railroad man was unable to stop the train and frantically blew his air 
horn to warn the children. 
</P>
<P>
 "Five of the kids hung off the side of the bridge," Sheriff's Sgt. Ron Merrill 
said, "but the 11-year-old took off running and didn't quite make it to the end 
of the bridge." 
</P>
<P>
 The name of the boy was withheld pending notice of next of kin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
