<HEADLINE>
<P>
FUND STARTED IN MEMORY OF SLAIN WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The family and friends of a woman slain in Orange last month have established 
a scholarship fund in her name. 
</P>
<P>
 Leanora Annette Wong, 23, was sexually assaulted and beaten to death May 20 
outside the Australian Beach Restaurant & Nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
 A convicted sex offender, Edward Patrick Morgan Jr., 28, was arrested several 
days later and now faces the possibility of the death sentence if convicted of 
killing the UC Riverside graduate. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund is a "living memorial scholarship for other young women who value 
education and have given of themselves to their family, school and community," 
according to a prepared statement. 
</P>
<P>
 Wong's memory "will live on in other young women who graduate from Ramona High 
School and continue to higher education," the statement said. 
</P>
<P>
 Contributions to the Lea Wong Memorial Scholarship Fund should be sent to: 
Riverside Campus Federal Credit Union, 3595 Canyon Crest Drive, Riverside, CA, 
92507-4697. 
</P>
</TEXT>
