<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA FIRE DESTROYS APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two people were burned out of their home Saturday when a fire that began in a 
closet destroyed their apartment, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokeswoman for the Santa Ana Fire Department said the fire, which was 
reported at 5:38 p.m., was contained to one apartment in a complex at 3800 S. 
Flower St. No one was in the apartment when the fire began. 
</P>
<P>
 Damage was estimated at $27,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators believe the cause of the fire was accidental, but the 
investigation continued late Saturday. The names of the occupants were not 
available. 
</P>
