VENTURA COUNTY BASEBALL STARS TO BE SHOWCASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County all-star baseball games have lost a bit of their luster but 
still will showcase most of the top players in two games today at Moorpark 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the three players of the year selected by the Ventura County coaches 
will not play in the large-school game, which pits top seniors from the 
Marmonte League against the Channel League.The game will begin at 1:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley outfielder Ryan Hankins (.483 average, nine homers) will play in 
the North-South all-star baseball series in Fresno this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Catcher Jeff Bennett (.356, seven homers) of Newbury Park will miss the game 
because of a family obligation, according to Westlake Coach Rich Herrera, coach 
of the Marmonte League all-stars. 
</P>
<P>
 The third player of the year, Jason Kimble (.481, four homers) of Buena, will 
try to give the Channel League its first victory in three years of the current 
alignment. Two years ago, the Channel League was no-hit in the first meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Herrera will have the services of Newbury Park pitcher Ray Clinton (10-3, 1.41 
ERA), Marmonte League pitcher of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 The first game will match seniors from the Tri-Valley League against the 
Frontier League at 10 a.m. Between games, players from both games will 
participate in a home run-hitting contest. MICHAEL LAZARUS 
