<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 DIE, CHILD HURT WHEN TRUCK CRASHES INTO RIVER BASIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man and a woman were killed and a child was injured early Saturday morning 
when all three were thrown from their truck after it jumped a guardrail on the 
Hollywood Freeway and landed in the Los Angeles River basin, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kasha Chmielinski, 3 1/2, who authorities said is the woman's daughter, was in 
fair condition late Saturday at Childrens Hospital in Los Angeles, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The dead were identified as Rafael Perez, 33, of Panorama City and Neisha 
Chmielinski, 24, of La Crescenta, according to a coroner's department 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims apparently were not wearing safety belts, said California Highway 
Patrol spokesman Frank Lewis. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 2:45 a.m., when Perez, traveling southbound on the 
Hollywood Freeway in the truck, attempted to merge onto the eastbound Ventura 
Freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that Perez was speeding, Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was going too fast, so he slides to the right and hits the guardrail," 
Lewis said. "Then he over-corrects, and crosses back over all four lanes to the 
left and hits the opposite guardrail." 
</P>
<P>
 After slamming into the second guardrail, the truck flipped over the side of 
the freeway, hit a tree and landed upside-down in the river basin, about 50 
feet below the freeway, Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash tore off the truck's fiberglass shell, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics pronounced Perez and Neisha Chmielinski dead at the scene, said Los 
Angeles Fire Department spokesman Brian Humphrey. 
</P>
<P>
 Kasha, who was found near her mother, told rescuers that another child had 
also been ejected in the crash, but authorities were unable to find anyone, 
Humphrey said. 
</P>
<P>
 "After an extensive search, it was determined that there was no other child, 
that (Kasha) was simply delirious," Humphrey said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident closed the eastbound Ventura Freeway at the interchange with the 
Hollywood Freeway for about an hour, Lewis said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
