<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAR CRASH LINKED TO BIRD CROSSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Simi Valley drivers were injured in a traffic accident that police say was 
caused when one of the drivers stopped to allow a covey of quail to cross the 
road. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirsten Lawrence, 26, and Jessica Vanderck, 22, were slightly injured in the 
accident that occurred about 3 p.m. Friday when Vanderck rear-ended Lawrence, 
who had stopped her car in the northbound lane of Erbes Road to allow the birds 
to pass, a Ventura County sheriff's deputy said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the car with Lawrence were her 7-year-old and 1-year-old daughters, as well 
as the family dog, the spokesman said.  
</P>
<P>
 Lawrence and Vanderck were taken to Los Robles Regional Medical Center, where 
they were treated for minor injuries and released, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 No citations were issued, and the quail were unharmed. 
</P>
