<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: BELL GARDENS; ESTRADA IS HIRED AS NEW CITY ATTORNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Estrada, who has served as interim city attorney, has been hired to 
the post by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Estrada's first task was to design a fee schedule that will save the city 
thousands of dollars annually in legal expenses.He has delivered his proposal 
to the city manager but would not discuss his fees until after the City Council 
sees them on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Henry Barbosa was fired as city attorney last summer, in part because his 
rates were too high. The city often paid $20,000 a month for his work. 
</P>
<P>
 Estrada, 38, works in the Downtown law firm of Richards, Watson & Gershon and 
plans to open an office in Bell Gardens City Hall. He said he will spend 20 to 
25 hours per week there. 
</P>
<P>
 Estrada also serves as assistant city attorney in Norwalk, South El Monte and 
La Puente. BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
