<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WESTLAKE; HOSPITAL DONATES SPACE TO POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For proponents of community-based policing, office space donated by the 
Hospital of the Good Samaritan to the Los Angeles Police Department is just 
what the doctor ordered. 
</P>
<P>
 Police officers from Rampart and other divisions will be able to use the space 
at 1254 W. 6th St. as a drop-in center to take crime reports, make phone calls 
and meet with residents and merchants without having to return to their station 
house. The center, in the Weingart Guest House on the hospital's grounds, 
opened last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
