<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOWLING THROUGH THE AGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN KING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A werewolf gave its first screen howl way back in 1935 in Universal Pictures' 
"Werewolf of London," which starred Henry Hull as a scientist-turned-wolf who 
terrorizes London. During the next six decades, no fewer than 40 movies 
featuring werewolves have been produced, plus two television series: 
</P>
<P>
 Werewolf of London (1935) The Wolf Man (1941) The Mad Monster (1942) 
Frankenstein Meets the Wolf Man (1943) The Return of the Vampire (1943) House 
of Frankenstein (1944) Cry of the Werewolf (1944) House of Dracula (1945) 
She-Wolf of London (1946) The Werewolf (1956) I Was a Teen-age Werewolf (1957) 
Face of the Screaming Werewolf (1959) The Curse of the Werewolf (1961) Werewolf 
in a Girl's Dormitory (1961) Munster Go Home! (1966) Mad Monster Party? (1967) 
Fury of the Wolf Man (1970) Werewolves on Wheels (1971) Dr. Jekyll and the Wolf 
Man (1971) The Rats Are Coming, The Werewolves Are Here (1972) Werewolf vs. the 
Vampire Women (1972) Moon of the Wolf (1972) The Werewolf of Washington (1973) 
The Beast Must Die (1974) Night of the Howling Beast (1975) Legend of the 
Werewolf (1975) Full Moon High (1981) The Howling (1981) An American Werewolf 
in London (1981) The Beast Within (1982) Silver Bullet (1985) Teen Wolf (1985) 
The Howling II: Your Sister Is a Werewolf (1985) The Company of Wolves (1985) 
Howling III (1987) Teen Wolf Two (1987) Deadtime Stories (1987) The Monster 
Squad (1987) Scooby and the Reluctant Werewolf (1988) Howling IV: The Original 
Nightmare (1988) Lone Wolf (1988) Howling V: The Rebirth (1989) Howling VI 
(1991) Mad at the Moon (1992) Wolf (1994) TV SERIES The Munsters (CBS: 1964-66) 
Werewolf (Fox: 1987-88) 
</P>
