<HEADLINE>
<P>
SATELLITE TECHNOLOGY OFFICIAL MOVES ON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Satellite Technology Management Inc. said Friday that its chief financial 
officer, Wayne Blair, is stepping down but will work as a consultant to the 
company for the next three months. 
</P>
<P>
 The parting is amicable, company spokesman Steve Strohman said.Blair, 55, was 
not available for comment. He joined the company as vice president of finance 
and chief financial officer in January, 1992, shortly after Satellite 
Technology went public. Before that, Blair had been a consultant to the 
company. 
</P>
<P>
 Strohman said the duties of chief financial officer and vice president of 
finance will be reassigned in coming months. 
</P>
<P>
 Satellite Technology makes and markets satellite communications networks. Most 
of its business is overseas. The company's stock, traded on the Nasdaq market, 
dropped 12.5 cents a share Friday to close at $7.50. 
</P>
