<P>
 Strep bacteria -- A story in The Times Saturday incorrectly described the 
so-called 'flesh-eating disease." Group A streptococcal infections, such as a 
rare condition that eats away at the filmy tissue surrounding muscles, are 
caused by a strain of the streptococcus bacteria. 
