<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP '94; WORLD CUP USA '94 / GROUP D PREVIEW; BULGARIA AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Grahame L. Jones 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * COACH: Dimitar Penev. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY PLAYERS: Hristo Stoichkov, Emil Kostadinov, Krasimir Balakov. 
</P>
<P>
 * STRENGTHS: There is enough firepower in the front line to provide the goals, 
with Stoichkov a world-class striker and Kostadinov having shown his touch in 
qualifying play.The defense is well marshaled by Petar Houbtchev. Balakov is a 
midfielder leader with a fine free kick. 
</P>
<P>
 * WEAKNESSES: Stoichkov's fiery temperament could land him in trouble with 
World Cup referees, who will be strict. If he is banished, Bulgaria's hopes 
will vanish because the team has no other truly outstanding performers. 
</P>
<P>
 * WORLD CUP HISTORY: Five previous appearances. Record of 0-10-6. Best finish 
was second round in Mexico '86. 
</P>
<P>
 * LITTLE-KNOWN FACT: Penev, the coach and former central defender, played in 
the 1966, 1970 and 1974 World Cup tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: In a group featuring four teams with obvious weaknesses, Bulgaria 
has the ability to make the second round. It should beat Greece and could cause 
Argentina problems in a potential free-for-all battle in Dallas in the last 
first-round match. 
</P>
<P>
