<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP '94; WORLD CUP USA '94 / GROUP D PREVIEW; GREECE AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Grahame L. Jones 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * COACH: Alkis Panagoulias. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY PLAYERS: Antonis Minou, Dimitris Saravakos, Tassos Mitropoulos. 
</P>
<P>
 * STRENGTHS: None to speak of, it seems. Goalkeeper Minou has experience and 
will need it, but he's 35.Saravakos boasts an excellent free kick, but he's 32. 
Mitropoulos provides the leadership and inspiration, but he's 36. 
</P>
<P>
 * WEAKNESSES: Far too many ancient Greeks. There are more over-30 players on 
the squad than on any other team. The defense is a shambles when faced by 
top-class opposition, and Argentina's Gabriel Batistuta, Nigeria's Rachidi 
Yekini and Bulgaria's Hristo Stoichkov will be lining up to take target 
practice. The team appears out of its depth at this level. 
</P>
<P>
 * WORLD CUP HISTORY: First appearance. 
</P>
<P>
 * LITTLE-KNOWN FACT: The Greek team's mascot in the tournament is a fox named 
Penelope, in honor of the Homeric heroine. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: After doing well to qualify, especially in finishing ahead of 
Russia, the Greeks have stumbled in warm-up games. They will have vociferous 
crowd support, but each of their three first-round opponents has the ability to 
defeat them and probably will. 
</P>
