<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP '94; WORLD CUP USA '94 / GROUP D PREVIEW; ARGENTINA AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Grahame L. Jones 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * COACH: Alfio Basile. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY PLAYERS: Gabriel Batistuta, Claudio Caniggia, Diego Maradona. 
</P>
<P>
 * STRENGTHS: Excellent forward line, with Italian-basedstarters Batistuta, 
Caniggia and Abel Balbo supplied by midfielders Maradona, Leonardo Rodrigues 
and Diego Simeone.Sergio Goycochea is the best penalty-stopping goalkeeper in 
the world but has been inconsistent lately and backup Luis Islas is being 
considered. 
</P>
<P>
 * WEAKNESSES: Defense is very suspect. Veteran Oscar Ruggeri is prone to 
injuries. Others have been exposed, particularly when confronted by speed. 
</P>
<P>
 * WORLD CUP HISTORY: Ten previous appearances. Record of 24-15-9. Winner in 
1978 and 1986; runner-up in 1930 and 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 * LITTLE-KNOWN FACT: Had then-coach Cesar Luis Menotti chosen Maradona for 
Argentina's 1978 World Cup team, this would have been Maradona's fifth World 
Cup, tying the record held by Mexico's Antonio Carbajal. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: A great deal depends on Maradona's ability to get the ball to the 
strikers. Argentina is capable of reaching the quarterfinals with relative 
ease, although either Nigeria or Bulgaria could upset it in the first round. 
Susceptible to being knocked out any time thereafter. 
</P>
<P>
