<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP '94; WORLD CUP USA '94 / GROUP F PREVIEW; BELGIUM AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Grahame L. Jones 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * COACH: Paul Van Himst. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY PLAYERS: Enzo Scifo, Marc Degryse, Josip Weber. 
</P>
<P>
 * STRENGTHS: Solid but unspectacular best describes the Belgians. Forward 
Degryse is an intelligent and experienced player, but all eyes will be on 
Croatian-born striker Weber, the top scorer in the Belgian League each of the 
past two seasons but a newcomer to the national team.Scifo is the midfield 
general and the team's finest playmaker. 
</P>
<P>
 * WEAKNESSES: Difficult to pinpoint, but lack of flair and imagination best 
sums it up. Goalkeeper Michel Preud'homme is experienced, although perhaps past 
his prime. 
</P>
<P>
 * WORLD CUP HISTORY: Eight previous appearances. Record of 7-14-4. Best finish 
was fourth place in Mexico in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 * LITTLE-KNOWN FACT: Van Himst, the coach, was Belgium's player of the year 
four times, the first time when he was only 16. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: No problems in the first round. The only question is, will Belgium 
or the Netherlands want to finish first in the group. The winner is likely to 
meet Brazil in the quarterfinals, while the runner-up might have an easier 
task. Gamesmanship could come into play. Unlikely to go beyond the final eight 
at best. 
</P>
<P>
 * PREDICTED FIRST-ROUND FINISH: Second. ROSTER 03,05,24,12 No. Name Position 1 
Michel Preud'homme Goalkeeper 12 Filip De Wilde Goalkeeper 20 Danny Verlinden 
Goalkeeper 2 Dirk Medved Defender 3 Vital Borkelmans Defender 4 Philippe Albert 
Defender 5 Rudy Smidts Defender 13 Georges Grun Defender 14 Michel De Wolf 
Defender 15 Marc Emmers Defender 22 Pascal Renier Defender 6 Lorenzo Staelens 
Midfielder 7 Franky Van der Elst Midfielder 10 Enzo Scifo Midfielder 16 Danny 
Boffin Midfielder 19 Eric Van Meir Midfielder 8 Luc Nilis Forward 9 Marc 
